les after the death of Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":22,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705197,"age":95,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Philip de Dodington was born in 1360, in Stafford, Staffordshire, England, his father, Henry Dodington, was 21 and his mother, Mrs. Henry Dodington, was 21. He had at least 1 son with Maud Matilda Laundey."},"et":{"1360–":"1360–Surnud","1360–Male":"1360–Surnud","–1645":"–1645","–1658":"–1658","–Female":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1350–Female":"1350–Surnud","1380–1428":"1380–1428","1340–Male":"1340–Surnud","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","1645":"1645","about 1380":"umbes 1380","1455":"1455","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1360":"1360","before 1360":"enne 1360","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","1428":"1428","1658":"1658","Stafford, Staffordshire, England":"Stafford, Staffordshire, England"},"fi":{"1360–":"1360–Kuollut","1360–Male":"1360–Kuollut","–1645":"–1645","–1658":"–1658","–Female":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1350–Female":"1350–Kuollut","1380–1428":"1380–1428","1340–